headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 37 points and hit several key shots in the fourth quarter as the Atlanta Hawks held on to beat the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers 127-121 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 37 as Hawks end 2-game skid with 127-121 win over short-handed 76ers

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 35 points and sparked a third-quarter rally to help the NBA-leading Boston Celtics get their 40th win of the season, 133-129 over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 35 points and Celtics ride 3rd-quarter rally to beat Wizards 133-129 for 40th win

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 25 points, RJ Barrett had 21 and the Toronto Raptors held on to beat Houston 107-104 on Friday night for their fourth straight home win over the Rockets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Immanuel Quickley scores 25 as Raptors beat Rockets 107-104 for 2nd straight victory

headlines.description: — Doc Rivers won his 1,099th regular-season game to move into eighth place on the NBA's list, Damian Lillard scored 26 points in his return from a two-game injury absence and the Milwaukee Bucks cruised past short-handed Charlotte 120-84 on Friday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Rivers wins No. 1,099 as Bucks trounce Hornets 120-84 to send Charlotte to its 10th straight loss

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 17 points, 17 rebounds and 10 assists to break a tie with Nikola Jokic for the NBA triple-double lead with 16 and the Sacramento Kings beat the Denver Nuggets 135-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis breaks tie with Jokic for NBA triple-double lead with 16, Kings rout Nuggets 135-106

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — D'Angelo Russell scored 30 points, Austin Reaves added 27 and the Los Angeles Lakers rode a spectacular 87-point first half to a 139-122 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers score 87 points in a spectacular first half and roll to a 139-122 victory over Pelicans
